From bded0f8410937dfea58b22b0d6e0cb3fb82c59b8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: CharlieChen114514 <725610365@qq.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 11:57:35 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: rtl8733bu -- wire into realtek Kconfig + Makefile

Register the ported RTL8733BU out-of-tree driver (wirenboard
v5.15.12-264_for6.18, ported in-tree for Linux 7.1) with the realtek
subsystem so CONFIG_RTL8733BU selects it. This is ONLY the 2-line
registration (source the Kconfig + add the obj-$(CONFIG) line); the
driver drop itself is materialized by
scripts/fetch-rtl8733bu-driver.sh (clone upstream + the forge overlay
under drivers/rtl8733bu/: hand-written Kbuild Makefile + fixed Kconfig
+ the cfg80211 wdev-wrapper patch). The wiring is a real git commit so
the tree stays clean -- the fetched rtl8733bu/ drop is gitignored.

Board-verified: document/logs/boot-sdl-202606201050.txt
(insmod -> probe RTL8733B -> fw from array -> wlan0/wlan1 ->
wpa_supplicant connects). Port roadmap: document/notes/29. Full pit
set: document/pitfalls/07.
---
 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Kconfig  | 1 +
 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile | 1 +
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile
index ab25419f5..38de4afdd 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile
@@ -9,4 +9,5 @@ obj-$(CONFIG_RTLWIFI)		+= rtlwifi/
 obj-$(CONFIG_RTL8XXXU)		+= rtl8xxxu/
 obj-$(CONFIG_RTW88)		+= rtw88/
 obj-$(CONFIG_RTW89)		+= rtw89/
+obj-$(CONFIG_RTL8733BU)		+= rtl8733bu/
 
